HEADWORD: Frumpish
<hw>Frump"ish</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Cross-tempered;
scornful.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Old-fashioned, as a woman's dress.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our Bell . . . looked very <qex>frumpish</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Foote.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Frush</ent>⟦br⟧
